                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d221">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">738.3915/244: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The High Commissioner in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">J. H. Russell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-07-14T14:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 14, 1923—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 6:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>100. Department’s 75, July 7, 5 p.m. President Borno has informed me that he
                    intends replying to my note accepting in principle <pb facs="0478" n="362"
                        xml:id="pg_362"/> the question of negotiating at this time with the
                    Dominican Government with a view to the settlement of the boundary dispute by
                    arbitration but that he will request that negotiations be carried on at Port au
                    Prince.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
